Ares of the rectangle problem in java:
Area of rectangle is the region occupied by a rectangle within its four sides or boundaries.
formula:Area of rectangle = Length x Breadth
        A = lb
import java.util.Scanner;
public class First_Project {
	public static void main(String[] args) {
		Scanner sc=new Scanner(System.in);
		System.out.print("Enter Leanth:");
		float leanth=sc.nextFloat();
		System.out.print("Enter breadth:");
		float breadth=sc.nextFloat();
		float Area=leanth*breadth;
		System.out.println("The area Rectanagle is "+Area);
	}
}
or we can do this program into another way also
public class First_Project {
	Scanner sc=new Scanner(System.in);
	public float Rectangle(){
		System.out.print("Enter leanth:");
		float leanth=sc.nextFloat();
		System.out.print("Enter breadth:");
		float breadth=sc.nextFloat();
		return leanth*breadth;
	}
	public static void main(String[] args) {
		 First_Project F1=new  First_Project();
		 System.out.println(F1.Rectangle());
		
	}
}
